ruleform.research.name: Testing only
ruleform.research.description: This rule is for testing purposes only. It is not 'real'.

ruleform.research.name: HumanProt Import
ruleform.research.description: A flag indicating that this rule is currently being used for importing HumanProt data into Ultra-Structure.

ruleform.relationship.name: is-a
ruleform.relationship.description: Taxonomic relationship indicating membership in a group or category.

ruleform.relationship.name: includes
ruleform.relationship.description: Taxonomic relationship defining membership in a group or category. In 'A includes B', A is the more general product, while B is some specialization or grouping of A

ruleform.relationship.name: mass-list
ruleform.relationship.description: A is a member of the mass list B

ruleform.relationship.name: mass-list-of
ruleform.relationship.description: A is a mass list that has B as a member

ruleform.relationship.name: ion-type
ruleform.relationship.description: A is an ion of type B

ruleform.relationship.name: ion-type-of
ruleform.relationship.description: A is the kind of ion that B is

ruleform.relationship.name: collection-type
ruleform.relationship.description: A is a collection of type B

ruleform.relationship.name: collection-type-of
ruleform.relationship.description: A is the kind of collection that B is

ruleform.attribute.name: CoRE Group Name Prefix
ruleform.attribute.description: The string used to generate sequential Product names for an object

ruleform.attribute.name: CoRE Group Name Sequence Object
ruleform.attribute.description: The Postgres Sequence Object used to generate sequential Product names for an object
ruleform.attribute.notes: The value of this attribute should be the name of a sequence object in the "sequences" schema. The "generate_*_from_group" functions use this attribute to generate new product names.
